Short summary

  • Improved floor plan editor
  • Improved application performance
  • Added ability to export guest book into CSV file
  • Improved user interface for server and zone management
  • Added page with online reservation form for each restaurant

Details

Ability to export guest book into CVS file

Now you can export all guest records into CVS file for marketing or other needs. If you navigate to guest book page you should see export icon in the toolbar. When you click export button you will be asked to confirm the export action,

In this release we are introducing a brand new reservation widget that you can place on your website. Not only does it come with a new style and different orientation options, it collects more information about your guests, such as email, food preferences, allergy, event type and more. Read about all these improvements below.


Example of the Widget on a Restaurant's Website

With just a few lines of JavaScript code, you can place a reservation widget on your website (Wix, Wordpress) or Facebook pages. You can find the code in the reservations section on the administrative portal.



Vertical or Horizontal Widget Options 

You can choose from the following available layouts for the widget: vertical or horizontal.

Collect More Information about Your Guests

We now help you collect not only a guest's name and phone number, but his or her email, food preferences, allergy, event type and special requests such as a stroller or high chair.
